      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8;">

        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
          Most storage facilities in the Uintah Basin are built with wood framing, plywood walls, and thin metal roll-up doors. In a fire, these structures burn fast — and everything inside goes with them. Fort Knox Self Storage is different. Every unit is an all-steel shipping container with zero combustible framing.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">Why Steel Containers Are Fire-Resistant</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Shipping containers are built from 14-gauge Corten steel — the same steel used in bridges and industrial construction. There are no wood studs, no plywood panels, no OSB sheathing, and no drywall that can serve as fuel in a fire. The steel walls, floor, and ceiling of each container create a sealed barrier that dramatically slows the spread of fire compared to any wood-frame storage building.</p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">24/7 Fire Detection Alerts</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Fort Knox Self Storage includes active fire detection across the facility. If a heat or smoke event is detected, alerts are triggered 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Most traditional storage facilities in Vernal have no fire detection at all — or rely on basic equipment that only activates during business hours.</p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">Protect What Matters</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">If you're storing irreplaceable items — family heirlooms, business records, hunting gear, tools, furniture — fire protection should be a deciding factor. The Uintah Basin's dry climate and seasonal wildfire risk make this even more important. Don't store your valuables in a building that would burn like kindling.</p>

